name: POWERFUL REVERSE THRUST | Delta Air Lines Boeing 717-200 Windy Landing in Minneapolis!
description:
And so ends my first 717 flight, seen here landing in Minneapolis after a two hour hop from Calgary! It was a great first flight on the 717, with a very windy approach and some great engine sounds from all the throttling up and down, along with some phenomenal sound on the landing roll from the reverse thrust. There'll be a trip report coming soon with the details of this flight, so stay tuned for that! Hope you enjoy this windy arrival into the Twin Cities.

Thanks for watching!

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

VIDEO LOG:
00:12 - Looking back at one of N993AT's BR715 engines.
00:35 - Descending into Minneapolis.
03:15 - Diving through the cloud layer.
10:30 - Flaps begin extending, some wind gusts pushing us around.
14:00 - Final approach with downtown Minneapolis in the background.
16:00 - Short final.
17:00 - Vacating runway 12L.
